sentences.english: Kratos bashes the man's head into the book yet again.

sentences.english: The temple on which Kratos stood, was the Sun Chariot of Helios.

sentences.english: Steven says, "Those McQuillanlanders (those people who live in McQuillanland) are my kind of people."

sentences.english: Tianyuan Kui Fan Zhuang is a good place to drink coffee.

sentences.english: Drain off the water in the pan through a strainer, and return the quinoa to the pan.

sentences.english: Kratos, there is not much time, Olympus needs you.

sentences.english: Kratos traverses the mountain cliffs and makes his way to Typhon's Cavern.

sentences.english: To this end, this "always Shengkui" class majority of people are Goyang naga-oriented.

sentences.english: “You don’t want to be in the same position for more than 30 minutes,” says Queiros.
sentences.chinese: 奎罗斯说，“你不想30多分钟都保持同一个姿势。”

sentences.english: Two of Quigley's insights had a particularly lasting impact.
sentences.chinese: 奎格利有两个见解对我有着特别持久的影响。

sentences.english: And what happened with you and Enrique Iglesias?

sentences.english: Kratoseventually is thrown onto a mountain summit.

sentences.english: Kratos is released from Atlas' grasp as the Titan laughs humorously .
sentences.chinese: 泰坦松开捏住奎托斯的手指，幽默地笑起来。
